original: Lindeberg, Karl Martin Lennart, med. lic., Skara, numera Stockholm, f. 15/5/10 i Ekeberga, Kronobergs 1., av glas mål. Karl Johan L. o. Martina Gustafsson. G. 1. 37-45 m. Vera Larsson; 2. 46 ni. Karla Knospe. Barn: Ulla f. 39, Mats 43. — Stud:ex. i Växjö 31, med. kand. 35 o. med. lic. 41 i Sthlm. Vik. å Maria sjukh. i Sthlm, Piteå las., Sahlgr. sjukh. i Gbg öronavd., Ekmanska sjukh. i Gbg, Malmö allm. sjukh., Eskilstuna las. öronavd. 41-44, des’sut. div. förordn. s. prov:-, stads- o. sjukstuguläk. Tf. prov:läk. i Skara distr. 47, praktik i Sthlm sed. 48. Hobhies : sport, konst.
translated:
Lindeberg, Karl Martin Lennart, Med. Lic., Skara, currently Stockholm, born on May 15, 1910 in Ekeberga, Kronoberg County, son of Karl Johan L. and Martina Gustafsson. Married 1. from 1937-1945 to Vera Larsson; 2. in 1946 to Karla Knospe. Children: Ulla, born in 1939, and Mats, born in 1943. 

Lindeberg graduated from Växjö Gymnasium in 1931, received his Bachelor of Medicine degree in 1935, and his Medical Licentiate degree in 1941, all in Stockholm. He worked temporarily at Maria Hospital in Stockholm, Piteå Hospital, Sahlgren Ear Department in Gothenburg, Ekman Hospital in Gothenburg, Malmö General Hospital, and Eskilstuna Hospital Ear Department from 1941-1944. He also served in various substitute positions as a district, city, and hospital physician. He was Acting District Physician in Skara from 1947 and has been practicing in Stockholm since 1948. His hobbies include sports and art.
